es\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"blue\",\"width\":3},\"name\":\"Taylor order 20\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Radius of Convergence: 1/(1+x^2)\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"black\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"range\":[-2.0,3.0],\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"black\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The Taylor polynomials match perfectly inside $|x| < 1$ but oscillate\nviolently beyond the radius of convergence. Higher order makes the\ndivergence **worse**, not better — a striking contrast to the entire-function\ncase above.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Multivariate Taylor [S+N]\n\nMaxima's `taylor` also handles multivariate expansions. Here we expand\n$\\sin(x)\\cos(y)$ around the origin to 4th order in both variables, then\ncompare the 3D surfaces.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Multivariate Taylor expansion */\nh : sin(x)*cos(y)$\nT_xy : taylor(h, [x, y], [0, 0], 4);\nT_xy_poly : ratdisrep(T_xy);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 94,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "x-(x^3+3*y^2*x)/6"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "x-{{3\\,x\\,y^2+x^3}\\over{6}}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 94,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* 3D surface: actual function */\nax_draw3d(\n  explicit(sin(x)*cos(y), x, -%pi, %pi, y, -%pi, %pi),\n  title=\"sin(x) cos(y)\", colorscale=\"Viridis\"\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 95,
      "outputs": [
